com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message

Class HttpDataMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpBaseMessage
      • com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpDataMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intel.icecp.core.Message, OnCommandMessage<HttpBridge_Module>, OnDataCommandMessage, Serializable

    public class HttpDataMessage
extends HttpBaseMessage
implements OnDataCommandMessage
    This message class is for the actual Http Requests. The setup command HttpSetupMessage returns the connectionId and the data command and command return channels to use for this message.

    Send Message

    Create a new HttpDataMessage( connectionId ) passing in the connectionId. The httpRequest field is also a required field. Once all the fields are setup for your Http request, then publish this message on the data command channel. If there is input data for the Http request (eg, form data) then publish that data on the inputChannel. The results of this command will be returned on the data command return channel.

    Results

    The same HttpDataMessage is returned on the data command return channel with the following filled in.

    status - The HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS of the call.

    responseHeaders - Response headers from the request.

    responseCode - The Http response code returned from the request.

    responseMessage - The Http response message returned from the request.

    Also, if there is any output from the Http request, it will be published to the output channel.

    • Field Detail

      • inputHttpChannelURI

        public URI inputHttpChannelURI
        (optional) The URI for the http input channel. Any input data required for the specified Http request is sent on this channel. The module will read the data from this channel and send it to the Http output stream for the Http request. For example any form data would be published on this channel.

      • inputTimeoutSeconds

        public long inputTimeoutSeconds
        (optional) Timeout value for the inputHttpChannelURI. This value specifies how many seconds the module will wait for data on the inputHttpChennelURI for the specified Http request. If the timeout expires, the module will no longer wait for input data and continue with the request. Default value is 30 seconds.

      • outputHttpChannelURI

        public URI outputHttpChannelURI
        (optional) The output channel URI where any output from the Http request is sent. If the Http request has any data on its input stream, it will be published to this channel.

      • urlPath

        public String urlPath
        (optional) Path information that is appended to the HttpSetupMessage.connectionUrl for this command. For example, if the connectionURL is http://myserver.com, this urlPath could be "/api/getName?id=1" creating a complete URL of: http://myserver.com/api/getName?id=1.

      • httpRequest

        public String httpRequest
        (Required) The actual Http request. No restrictions on this, the string is sent directly to the Http server. Typical values are GET, PUT, POST, DELETE, HEAD.

      • requestHeaders

        public Map<String,String> requestHeaders
        (optional) Specify the Http request headers in the Map. The format is name value pairs. Example: "Content-Language", "en-US". These values are sent directly to the Http request.

      • useCache

        public boolean useCache
        (required) Specify whether you want the Http request to use any cached values. True means it is ok to used cached values. False means do not use cached data. Default is false;

      • responseHeaders

        public Map<String,List<String>> responseHeaders
        These headers are returned from the Http request. The number of headers and values depends on the Http request.

      • responseCode

        public int responseCode
        The response code returned from the Http request.

      • responseMessage

        public String responseMessage
        The response message returned from the Http Request.
